verbose_text: As was expected, miR-144-3p mimics markedly upregulated the protein level of the epithe-lial marker, E-cadherin, and downregulated the expression of the mesenchymal marker, N-cadherin, in the CAL-27 and SCC-4 cells, suggesting that miR-144-3p suppressed the EMT process (XREF_FIG).
evidence: expression of the mesenchymal marker, N-cadherin
